com.castlabs.sdk.conviva

Class ConvivaPlugin

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.castlabs.android.Plugin
      • com.castlabs.sdk.conviva.ConvivaPlugin

  • public class ConvivaPlugin
extends com.castlabs.android.Plugin
    This plugin integrates Conviva Analytics with the castLabs Player SDK.

    You can enable and register the plugin before you initialize the SDK: 

    
  public class MyApp extends Application {
      @Override
      public void onCreate() {
          super.onCreate();

          ConvivaPlugin conviva = new ConvivaPlugin();
          // use the conviva plugin instance before registering it
          // to modify the system or client settings
          try {
              conviva.getClientSettings().gatewayUrl = CONVIVA_TOUCHSTONE_GATEWAY;
              PlayerSDK.register(conviva);
          } catch (Exception e) {
              Log.e(TAG, "Invalid Conviva customer key!");
          }

          PlayerSDK.register(conviva);
          PlayerSDK.init(getApplicationContext());
      }
 }

    Please note that you can customize the client settings (see getClientSettings() and the system settings (see getSystemSettings()) before you register the plugin.

      • getSystemSettings

        public com.conviva.api.SystemSettings getSystemSettings()
        Access the system settings that will be used to initialize the Conviva SystemInterface.

        Note: If you are making modification to the system settings, please make sure you do so before you register the plugin. Once the plugin is initialized, changing system settings might now have an effect.

        Returns:
        The system settings
